rComments: Encourages questions in class and helpful in person. Sympathetic and approachable. Problem sets were 50% simple questions/50% difficult ones, with concepts closely related to what was covered in class (usually). Always posted pset/midterm solutions in a timely manner.
Bovy taught AST222 pretty nicely. Overall solid class, problem sets are hard, very interesting material however!

Jo was an amazing instructor, very clear lectures that are supported by remarkably clear notes. His notes are so good you will never need to look at the textbook! His assignments are hard but they are a great learning experience. I would highly recommend!

AVOID: 1. Does NOT provide lecture notes. 2. Lectures are monotonous, poorly paced. 3. Problem sets are challenging, but unlike 221, he explicitly discourages seeking assistance (derides you) and actively dissuades TAs from helping students. 4. Outside of class, cynical and unsympathetic. 5. Many expletives I have refrained from using.

He really seems to believe in Laissez Faire in his teaching. He is not overly fond of questions during class, doesn't have regular office hours, and the weekly problem sets are distributed sporadically and seldom related to the topics covered in class. Generally sort of awkward.
